            <bug_when>2010-10-01 10:32:16 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>As can be seen with dependency logging, all &#39;implement&#39; and &#39;include&#39; 
dependencies are already correctly detected by the generator and included as 
load-time dependencies. It is just not apparent in the code :-/.

Assump.: As dependency detection is done by traversing the syntax tree, 
&#39;implement&#39; and &#39;include&#39; map values are inspected as well, and it obviously 
suffices that the contained identifiers are outside a function context, in 
order to classify them as load-time deps. (The question here is, why is the 
&#39;extend&#39; key, which is basically the same in this respect,  treated 
*explicitly* in the code?!).</thetext>
